message:
@gcauchon I don't think so. The reason is that this is a decision that the user of the framework should make:

* Open Source Applications: Shoud probably have it
* Closed Source Applications: Most companies do not want to expose their unminified JS. If using Sentry for example a `hidden-source-map` can be used and uploaded instead.

@brightball thanks for bringing those points! I think your concerns are valid but our intention is to start simple and build only the bootstrap for users to send emails. For most applications this is enough. 

The applications that are using _umbrella_ can use the "--context-app" flag when using the "phx.gen.notifier"  which allows the files to be generated in a specific app. This can achieve the isolation you mentioned.

For more complex cases I think it's up to the user to come with a better arrangement for its app, because it can vary a lot from case to case. I think the community can help with documentation - like your blog post, or guides - but the framework shouldn't delimit the lines for those scenarios IMHO.

Update channels.md

